{
  "stem": "10572.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if you would have asked me for my religion, I would have said, I'm a Jew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went to-- after I became six years old I went to a [NON-ENGLISH], which was the Jewish primary school across the street from our synagogue.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had-- it was a two class-- classroom school, but a very, very good school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So good that I remember that two Christian students attended the school because their parents wanted them to get the education that Lehrer Stern, our teacher, and Lehrer Bach would give us.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went to that school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were-- we had to go for four years to primary school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was an exception made.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If you had particularly good grades, you could finish after three years.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And after three years, you would take an exam to go into the school that my parents had picked for me, Gymnasium [?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Josefino. ?] A gymnasium was a school that prepared you-- it was really a combination of-- of high school and junior college.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you had to pass a very tough examination in order to be admitted to the school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I remember that friend of mine who had gone with me to this Jewish primary school, Hans Pallenbaum, and I, were of 78 students accepted, the two who made the top grades.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was told later on, when I didn't perform as well as they-- as those teachers had expected, that there were two teachers of two different classes who had fought for these two Jewish boys to get them in their class because they had high expectations, and I didn't fulfill those high expectations.",
      "word_count": 54
    }
  ],
